## Overview
Comprehensive testing strategy to ensure all TL;DR page enhancements work correctly, are accessible, performant, and don't regress existing functionality.

## Testing Philosophy
- **Test-Driven Where Possible**: Write tests before or alongside implementation
- **Detailed Logging**: All tests should log their actions for debugging
- **Isolation**: Unit tests mock dependencies, E2E tests use real browser
- **Coverage**: Aim for 80%+ coverage on new code

## Test Categories

### 1. Unit Tests
- New utility functions (formatStarCount, etc.)
- New React components in isolation
- Custom hooks
- State management logic

### 2. Integration Tests
- Component interactions
- State flow between components
- Event handling chains

### 3. E2E Tests (Playwright)
- Complete user flows
- Cross-browser compatibility
- Mobile/desktop viewports
- Keyboard navigation paths

### 4. Accessibility Tests
- axe-core automated scans
- Manual screen reader testing checklist
- Keyboard-only navigation verification
- Focus management validation

### 5. Performance Tests
- Lighthouse CI integration
- Animation frame rate monitoring
- Bundle size budgets
- Time to interactive benchmarks

## Key Files
- `tests/e2e/tldr.spec.ts` - Existing E2E tests (MUST UPDATE)
- `tests/unit/` - New unit test directory
- `tests/accessibility/` - Accessibility test scripts
- `playwright.config.ts` - Playwright configuration

